_header: Tread eke thee kenneth / Sunday what letter on runneth
_description: Verse within Henry Daniel’s Liber Uricrisiarum or Dome of Urines, in Book II, chapter 6 — four couplets of very rough meter

HunHM505.Transcription:
Tred eke the kennythSonday whate letter on rennythEt in whate
                    yereof the of þe solcield wythowtyn any werefferste daye of
                    þe yereflette the threde forthe pryk to the nereEt at the ferthe
                    Lope-yere while þou lyuist in erthe
HunHM505.Note:
Written as prose around a circular table, with colophon,
                        ‘Nascitur proprie Nos et Garlandus’ (f.
                    60v)/
